Fresh-eyes review complete for `src/blog/people/drafts/Kaia-Gerber.md`. The notes were appended as a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-07-10)` comment block at the bottom of the file — no body edits were made.

The two biggest issues flagged:

1. **The 99-seat play is over-leveraged.** It's retold five times (intro, TL;DR, FAQ, black-box section, ending), and the intro already gives away its interpretation, so the climactic section arrives pre-summarized. The fix is to keep the intro's image but save the meaning for the payoff.
2. **The family is only Cindy.** Rande Gerber never appears, and brother Presley — same house, same privilege, opposite public outcome (the 2020 "Misunderstood" face tattoo flameout, which I verified is a real, well-covered theme) — is the missing control group for the piece's central thesis that inherited ground never feels like ground.

Other notable flags: the dating section asserts a redemption arc the body doesn't show (the Rabbit Hole holds the 9-merge tension honestly, but the body picks a side), Library Science is presented as solo when it's co-founded with Alyssa Reeder (the partnership actually helps the Six reading), and "safety to fail" repeats seven times across the file. On the preserve list: the reading-list dossier, the Minghella screenshot tell, and the way critic pressure is genuinely conceded before the lens turn.

Sources from the reality check: [Library Science — About](https://libraryscience.net/about), [Fashion Week Daily on Presley's face tattoo](https://fashionweekdaily.com/presley-gerber-face-tattoo-transphobia/), [Hollywood Authentic — Kaia Gerber](https://hollywoodauthentic.com/kaia-gerber/) (sobriety turned up no confirmed public theme, so I left it out).
